observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

Fast track the system upgrade of the Municipality’s ETRACS for the generation of reports needed by the Accountable Officers and Acting Municipal Treasurer in the preparation of the RAAF and CRAAF, respectively;

Compel the Accountable Officers and Acting Municipal Treasurer to manually prepare RAAF and CRAAF in case of system downtimes in the ETRACS and submit the CRAAF in accordance with the timeline.

For the improvement and efficiency of operation of Plaridel Water System, we recommend that management:

Formulate a Comprehensive Operations Manual involving the core processes of PWS such as Meter-Reading, Billing, Collection, Remittance, Monitoring of Receivables and Disconnection of water services, including but not limited to the following:
Rename the Notice of Collection to Notice of Billing to be prepared in two copies and enhance the data by including prior period account balances as well as notifying the consumers of possible service disconnection;
Segregate the cash control function and the recording of transaction to eliminate errors or fraud by requiring the Billing Section to maintain the Customer Ledger Cards;
Require the Billing Section to regularly update the Customer Ledger Cards and include a column for outstanding balance;
Strengthen collection efforts by enjoining the Collection Section by imposing penalty on late payments and disconnecting water services for accounts which are past due for over 2 months; and
Require the Billing Department to submit monthly Billing Statements to Accounting which will be the basis in establishing Accounts Receivable from Waterworks System Fees to be reported in the financial statements.

Exert extensive efforts to collect delinquent accounts and disconnect water lines if no payment is made within the agreed period of time.

We recommend that management:

Direct the Municipal Accountant and GSO to prepare and maintain Supplies Ledger Card (SLC) and Stock Card (SC), respectively;

Enjoin the GSO to:

Submit weekly Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) to the Municipal Accountant as basis for the recording of expenses for inventories consumed or distributed;

Comply with the semestral submission of the Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RPCI).

We recommended that Local Chief Executive undertake the following measures:

Enjoin the Accounting and Treasury Office to reconcile their records at least quarterly, prior to the preparation of financial reports to avoid accumulation of variance;
Require the Municipal Accountant to record only transactions that actually occur within the reporting period to ensure accuracy of Financial Statements;
Require the Municipal Treasurer to return the unutulized balance from the National Housing Authority (NHA) projects and consequently close its corresponding bank account;
Require the MPDO to expedite the implementation of the Bangus Production in cages project funded under BUB in order to avoid the designated bank account becoming inactive;
Direct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile their records pertaining to LBP Account Nos. 1292-1093-65 and 1292-1151-95 and to subsequently close the said accounts in the books of the LGU;
Instruct the Acting Municipal Treasurer to formally close the LBP Account No. 4212-1037-00 in order not to incur unnecessary expense. Henceforth ensure that all accounts planned for closure are formally closed through the appropriate bank procedures; and
Require the Municipal Treasurer to transfer bank accounts from LBP Oroquieta Branch to the nearer LBP Agrihub Branch in Plaridel to streamline the number of accounts to be monitored. Additionally, promptly update external agencies such as PhilHealth and BIR about the new account details.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:

Require the GSO and Municipal Accountant - for current purchases onwards-to religiously prepare and maintain the Property Cards and PPE Ledger Cards, and reconcile both records regularly pending completion of one-time cleansing;
Instruct the GSO - Designate to issue PAR to end users for all issuances of property and equipment;
Given the enormity of workload involving one time-cleansing of PPE, consider implementing the PPE cleansing by phase (i.e. by PPE class). Thereafter, require Inventory Committee and the Accountant to submit to the audit Team the reports and documents required under COA Circular No. 2020-006 as appropriate, for verification, and
Instruct the Inventory Committee to conduct physical count annually and to prepare report on the physical count of properties in order to monitor existence of the said properties, not to mention their physical condition.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Direct its Municipal Accountant validate all documents available supporting the Accounts Payable outstanding for two years or more, send notices to identified creditors affected for possible claim, and if still not claimed within reasonable period of time, cause reversion to the Unappropriated Surplus pursuant to Section 98 of PD 1445; and
Instruct the Municipal Accountant to maintain Subsidiary Ledger and prepare a schedule detailing the name of creditor, nature of transaction and amount for ease in monitoring;

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Require the Municipal Disaster Risk and Reduction Council, through the MDRRMO, to revisit and reassess the projects listed in the Annual Investment Plan for capital outlay and identify and prioritize only the most critical or urgent undertaking instead of spreading thinly the appropriation across several projects which may compromise the impact and effectiveness of implementation; and;
Require the Project Monitoring Committee to include in its monitoring and evaluation all programs, projects, and activities of the municipality, not limited to infrastructure-related undertakings.

In view of the foregoing circumstances, we recommend that:

Management revisits the work load of the BAC secretariat to address manpower requirements needed to comply with the documentary requirements; 
BAC members, BAC secretariat and the Technical Working Group familiarize themselves with Revised IRR of RA No. 9184 with regard to procurement planning, invitation to observers, and posting requirement, among others, to enhance transparency and to establish the regularity of the procurement process;  
Compel the BAC to submit lacking supporting documents; 

Require the Municipal Engineer to ensure that all necessary documentary requirements related to the construction of projects are submitted prior to certifying the completion of the projects.

We recommend that management direct the GSO:

To request a copy of documents from the LTO for those motor vehicles which documents necessary for registration cannot be located;

To process the renewal of the Isuzo Forward Dump truck that was not renewed due to change engine by preparing the documents required by LTO;

