We recommend the following:

Create an inventory committee composed of adequate number 
of members with at least one member each from the Accounting Unit and the GSO and enjoin them to conduct the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts of the Municipality in accordance with the prescribed procedures embodied in COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 to establish PPE balances that are verifiable as to existence, condition and accountability;

After the conduct of inventory taking, direct the inventory committee to prepare and submit the following to the Audit Team in the prescribed format:

Report on Physical Count of PPE (RPCPPE);

Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP), if there are unserviceable properties found during inventory taking;

Request for Relief from Accountability by Accountable persons for lost PPE items under their accountability, if any;

Journal Entry Vouchers drawn by the Accounting Unit for recognition of loss of PPE from concerned accountable officers/personnel, if any, and other necessary adjusting entries.

We recommend the Management to:

Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare Journal Entry Voucher to record the donated agri-machineries in the books of the LGU based on the documents evidencing the transfer from PHILMECH for proper presentation in the financial statements;

Require all offices to furnish the Municipal Accountant a copy of the Memorandum of Agreement and Deed of Donation concerning all donations in kind received by the Municipality in the future;

Direct the Municipal Agriculturist to make series of follow-ups to PHILMECH to expedite the repair of the agri-machineries; if unrepaired by June 30,2023, return the equipment to the source agency.

