We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a. require his liaison officer to immediately submit the LR of the CY 2019 CA voucher to the ICFAU together with its supporting documents;

b. facilitate the submission of the CY 2020 CA voucher to the Audit Team and its LR to the ICFAU, all supported with the necessary documentary requirements;

c. submit to the Municipal Accountant the duly received LR for CY 2020 CA voucher and require him to record the liquidation; and

d. ensure that the CA for CF is granted only after the liquidation of the previous CA and that all CAs are liquidated at year-end.

We have recommended that management:

Execute contract of lease for all heavy equipment lease transactions to cover the terms and conditions of the lease agreement;

Submit computations to support the rental rates;

Maintain equipment logbooks showing the time and date of release and return of the heavy equipment;

Require duly approved trip tickets for every release of heavy equipment; and

Instruct the GSO to keep custody of the equipment keys and verify details of trip tickets vis-à-vis the amount paid and require the lessee for payments of deficiencies, if any.

